The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Nov. 26: MIRC Electronics founder and chairman Gulu Mirchandani is preparing to pass the baton on to the next generation. The company today announced that Mirchandani had halved his stake in the company, transferring 17.56 per cent stake to his two sons. Mirc Electronics sells the Onida brand of consumer durables.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 26: Sebi today asked the bourses to amend the debt-listing agreement making it mandatory for companies to maintain adequate security cover at all times for corporate bonds and other debt instruments.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 26: Cash-strapped Air India may be heading for another strike after the meeting between the pilots and the airline management remained inconclusive today.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 26: ArcelorMittal may set up a steel plant in the mineral-rich state of Chhattisgarh. Chhattisgarh chief minister Raman Singh said the company had approached his government with a mega investment plan.                                                                                                                          
